<div class="article-body-content"><p dir="ltr" style="" class="">Every night, <a href="http://www.adaa.org/understanding-anxiety/related-illnesses/sleep-disorders">40 million</a> Americans lie awake while stress and anxiety make their mental cylinders fire. They turn a rough day at work into a repeating string of lousy song lyrics or an intense need to replay a breakup that happened a decade ago. They watch the clock, deciding sleep is out of their grasp. And what's worse, they don't know how to make it stop.</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="" class="">Evidence <a href="http://mic.com/articles/127658/why-meditation-helps-you-have-better-sex">suggests</a> meditation could help reduce the stress plaguing so many people. But that would mean, you know, <a href="http://mic.com/articles/125370/i-test-the-headspace-meditation-app-to-try-to-train-my-brain-to-chill">learning to meditate</a>. Fortunately, there's an absurdly easy trick based on the same principles. I use it. I recommend it. The only thing you need to know is how to count.</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="" class="">It's called the 4-7-8 breathing technique, also known as Relaxing Breath. According to <a href="http://www.drweil.com/drw/u/ART00521/three-breathing-exercises.html">Dr. Andrew Weil</a>, it's a natural depressant for your nervous system, helping you fall asleep in&nbsp;<a href="http://www.goodhousekeeping.co.uk/health/health-advice/new-breathing-trick-puts-you-to-sleep-in-seconds">60 seconds</a>&nbsp;by quieting the parts of your brain where stress manifests.</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="">This is how you do it, <a href="http://www.drweil.com/drw/u/ART00521/three-breathing-exercises.html">according to</a>&nbsp;Weil's website:</p>
<h3 style="">1. Press the tip of your tongue against the hard ridge of tissue behind your upper front teeth and keep it there.</h3>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix embeddable-gif image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small" id="embeddable-3gi977o" data-type="gif"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://gifs.mic.com/2upixf7xt1yfwvhmwyptpolpj8f1j6r4nxyfinqcyp3spjw1unvphl1ifhvhf2mz.gif" alt="There's One Sleep Trick That Actually Works &mdash; Here's the Science Behind Why" data-original-src="http://images.mic.com/2upixf7xt1yfwvhmwyptpolpj8f1j6r4nxyfinqcyp3spjw1unvphl1ifhvhf2mz.gif" data-gif-src="http://thumbs.mic.com/YTQ2NWFkOGRmYyMvZVRkdlk5dG5TeWYyWjU3bm15Q2tUTXpodVFJPS9maXQtaW4vOTAweDkwMC9maWx0ZXJzOm5vX3Vwc2NhbGUoKTpxdWFsaXR5KDgwKS9odHRwOi8vaW1hZ2VzLm1pYy5jb20vMnVwaXhmN3h0MXlmd3ZobXd5cHRwb2xwajhmMWo2cjRueHlmaW5xY3lwM3NwancxdW52cGhsMWlmaHZoZjJtei5naWY=.gif" data-video-src="http://thumbs.mic..gif" class="graceful-gif"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gz4G31LGyog" class="article-embeddable-source">YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<h3 style="">2. Exhale all of your breath out.</h3>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix embeddable-gif image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small" id="embeddable-v5viv" data-type="gif"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://gifs.mic.com/qpuge0ot9nvm97f0wcnsjhp9jdyq51iut1r6xct5rdzv8zprkwkcbhadvqguxxjg.gif" alt="There's One Sleep Trick That Actually Works &mdash; Here's the Science Behind Why" data-original-src="http://images.mic.com/qpuge0ot9nvm97f0wcnsjhp9jdyq51iut1r6xct5rdzv8zprkwkcbhadvqguxxjg.gif" data-gif-src="http://thumbs.mic.com/ZTFlMzBmYmMxOCMvT2JsRGNvdEcwbW5VeXNxT1dCX2Zpdmp1QjFNPS9maXQtaW4vOTAweDkwMC9maWx0ZXJzOm5vX3Vwc2NhbGUoKTpxdWFsaXR5KDgwKS9odHRwOi8vaW1hZ2VzLm1pYy5jb20vcXB1Z2Uwb3Q5bnZtOTdmMHdjbnNqaHA5amR5cTUxaXV0MXI2eGN0NXJkenY4enBya3drY2JoYWR2cWd1eHhqZy5naWY=.gif" data-video-src="http://thumbs.mic..gif" class="graceful-gif"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gz4G31LGyog" class="article-embeddable-source">YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<h3 style="">3. Inhale, quietly, through your nose for four seconds.</h3>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix embeddable-gif image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small" id="embeddable-1taq3ig" data-type="gif"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://gifs.mic.com/bgaez9reu28tivoda7zwzwnfvrzjvlyjutr3mb89fbttegmzmviusmgbifkoqazu.gif" alt="There's One Sleep Trick That Actually Works &mdash; Here's the Science Behind Why" data-original-src="http://images.mic.com/bgaez9reu28tivoda7zwzwnfvrzjvlyjutr3mb89fbttegmzmviusmgbifkoqazu.gif" data-gif-src="http://thumbs.mic.com/NTQwZTg5OGQxMCMvWWU5R3J4by02dXpVWThHc0h3NzgzWkpxM2MwPS9maXQtaW4vOTAweDkwMC9maWx0ZXJzOm5vX3Vwc2NhbGUoKTpxdWFsaXR5KDgwKS9odHRwOi8vaW1hZ2VzLm1pYy5jb20vYmdhZXo5cmV1Mjh0aXZvZGE3end6d25mdnJ6anZseWp1dHIzbWI4OWZidHRlZ216bXZpdXNtZ2JpZmtvcWF6dS5naWY=.gif" data-video-src="http://thumbs.mic..gif" class="graceful-gif"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gz4G31LGyog" class="article-embeddable-source">YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<h3 style="">4. Hold that breath for seven seconds.</h3>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix embeddable-gif image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small" id="embeddable-34l1d98" data-type="gif"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://gifs.mic.com/h4wlid6dyxdsp2o7nbwbu0a6z8zprrhsjhnttsxkmz7u4uizg2zids4rnafcsyla.gif" alt="There's One Sleep Trick That Actually Works &mdash; Here's the Science Behind Why" data-original-src="http://images.mic.com/h4wlid6dyxdsp2o7nbwbu0a6z8zprrhsjhnttsxkmz7u4uizg2zids4rnafcsyla.gif" data-gif-src="http://thumbs.mic.com/OTNhYmQxN2E2OCMvZWh2WXVsVTNkOEVYZnhKN2FxZjRjc0ZQa3Y4PS9maXQtaW4vOTAweDkwMC9maWx0ZXJzOm5vX3Vwc2NhbGUoKTpxdWFsaXR5KDgwKS9odHRwOi8vaW1hZ2VzLm1pYy5jb20vaDR3bGlkNmR5eGRzcDJvN25id2J1MGE2ejh6cHJyaHNqaG50dHN4a216N3U0dWl6ZzJ6aWRzNHJuYWZjc3lsYS5naWY=.gif" data-video-src="http://thumbs.mic..gif" class="graceful-gif"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gz4G31LGyog" class="article-embeddable-source">YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<h3 style="">5. Exhale completely through your mouth, making a whooshing sound, for eight seconds.</h3>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix embeddable-gif image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small" id="embeddable-a1279s8" data-type="gif"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://gifs.mic.com/qsupdekdyjbsyji9eqdjaaarvbzocqgbhlbkuy1mlt1wbwb3yrphqhhpaai2m3fl.gif" alt="There's One Sleep Trick That Actually Works &mdash; Here's the Science Behind Why" data-original-src="http://images.mic.com/qsupdekdyjbsyji9eqdjaaarvbzocqgbhlbkuy1mlt1wbwb3yrphqhhpaai2m3fl.gif" data-gif-src="http://thumbs.mic.com/ZDk4NDZkNmI3NSMvRHJKTjVQYnNueDgxMnJhTGhNWXNXbE9vckRRPS9maXQtaW4vOTAweDkwMC9maWx0ZXJzOm5vX3Vwc2NhbGUoKTpxdWFsaXR5KDgwKS9odHRwOi8vaW1hZ2VzLm1pYy5jb20vcXN1cGRla2R5amJzeWppOWVxZGphYWFydmJ6b2NxZ2JobGJrdXkxbWx0MXdid2IzeXJwaHFoaHBhYWkybTNmbC5naWY=.gif" data-video-src="http://thumbs.mic..gif" class="graceful-gif"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gz4G31LGyog" class="article-embeddable-source">YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<h3 style="">6. Repeat the cycle four times.</h3>
<p dir="ltr" class="">Boom. You're out.</p>
<p dir="ltr" class=""><b>How it works:</b> "Sleep is a vulnerable state and it takes body-wide permission to achieve,"&nbsp;Joseph Chandler, an assistant professor of psychology at Birmingham-Southern College,&nbsp;told&nbsp;<i>Mic</i>. "Feedback from different systems, including the stress system, must give the green light that it is safe to sleep."</p>
<p dir="ltr" class="">Relaxing Breath is a means of halting the hypothalamus, pituitary and adrenal gland cascade &mdash; called the HPA axis &mdash; responsible for stress reactions. When the HPA axis is activated, your ability to fall asleep and stay asleep is compromised.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The HPA cascade might cause your brain to start to "freak out" &mdash; your anxiety is keeping you wired. When you break the cascade, the feeling of relaxation tells your brain all systems are go, you're finally safe. "This manifests in the appearance of alpha brain waves, the initial indication of entering the first stage of sleep," said Chandler.</p>
<p class="">Why is it so effective? "To my knowledge there is nothing specific about the timing that makes this technique work," Chandler told <i>Mic</i>. There are several variants of this pattern, he said, but the basics are all the same, "inhale slowly, hold and exhale with some force." It's similar to <a href="http://www.lamaze.org/lamazebreathing">Lamaze breathing</a>, the procedure taught in some prepared childbirth classes. Each method is predicated on the same concept of systemic stress reduction.&nbsp;</p>
<p class="">The 4-7-8 method is a quick and easy way to relieve your anxiety just enough to crash. As you get better with the technique, it could hopefully prevent you from sleepless nights in the future.</p>
<figure contenteditable="false" data-youtube-id="gz4G31LGyog" class="embeddable clearfix embeddable-video embeddable-youtube" id="embeddable-v1ab89" data-type="youtube">
  <div class="embeddable-container">
    <div class="lazyYT" data-youtube-id="gz4G31LGyog" data-ratio="16:9"></div>
  </div>
  <figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gz4G31LGyog" class="article-embeddable-source">YouTube</a></figcaption>
</figure></div>
